@Email.API_HostAddress = https://localhost:7006

### Health Check
GET {{Email.API_HostAddress}}/health

### Send Email Asynchronously (via RabbitMQ)
POST {{Email.API_HostAddress}}/api/email/send-async
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "recipient@example.com",
  "subject": "Test Email from Cinemax",
  "body": "<h1>Hello from Cinemax!</h1><p>This is a test email sent via our microservice.</p>",
  "isHtml": true,
  "priority": 1
}

### Send Email Synchronously (for testing)
POST {{Email.API_HostAddress}}/api/email/send-sync
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "recipient@example.com",
  "subject": "Sync Test Email from Cinemax",
  "body": "This is a test email sent synchronously.",
  "isHtml": false,
  "priority": 1
}

### Send Email with CC and BCC
POST {{Email.API_HostAddress}}/api/email/send-async
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "recipient@example.com",
  "subject": "Email with CC and BCC",
  "body": "<h2>Important Notification</h2><p>This email has CC and BCC recipients.</p>",
  "isHtml": true,
  "cc": ["cc1@example.com", "cc2@example.com"],
  "bcc": ["bcc@example.com"],
  "priority": 2
}

### Send High Priority Email
POST {{Email.API_HostAddress}}/api/email/send-async
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "urgent@example.com",
  "subject": "URGENT: High Priority Email",
  "body": "<h1 style='color: red;'>URGENT</h1><p>This is a high priority email.</p>",
  "isHtml": true,
  "priority": 2
}


